summary: Leak Discussion
body:
Leak Discussion

So I haven’t seen the source for these new leaks so I’m not quite sure what they are, but I have seen one thing that I want to talk about. If you don’t want to discuss possible spoilers skip the post now.

Jon reforming the Night’s Watch is the absolute stupidest thing I have ever fucking heard. This wouldn’t be bittersweet, this would be idiotic with the story that D&D have written. I can only hope that if this is coming from a reliable leaker it’s because the showrunners are doing damage control with fake leaks, because that is the absolute height of idiocy. Why? You ask, Jon decided to dedicate his life to the Night’s Watch, it’s an ancient institution that his family has been a part of for thousands of years! Sure you don’t like the ending, but D&D did say it was bittersweet.

Yes, well, uh, answer me this, intrepid viewer… WHAT THE FUCK WOULD THEY BE WATCHING?????????????

It has been well established that the Wall wasn’t actually built to keep the Wildlings in, it was built to try to prevent the White Walkers from coming south. And even if it were there for the Wildlings, do you really think Jon’s going to round them all up and send them back into their frozen wasteland again?

There is nothing for the Night’s Watch to fucking watch!!!! What on Earth would be the point of reforming it?!

The only way I could maybe see this happen is if the Night’s Watch becomes some sort of IDEK, army for the Starks????? But that wouldn’t be the Night’s Watch?????

Now, I could understand the Night’s Watch reforming in the books, if the defeat of the Others goes differently and they get pushed back behind the wall. I could see the Night’s Watch then reforming. But, uh, D&D??? Yeah guys that DOESNT WORK IN THE SHOW VERSE YOU FUCKING MORONS?

These leaks cannot be completely real. Someone has found a credible leaker source and slapped them so hard with the threat of a lawsuit that they regurgitated whatever fake leaks the show wanted. If this is real then it will be proof that the showrunners didn’t care about the show and figured they’d do whatever in the final season because it’s not like the fans could do anything about it by then.

summary: Jon has no claim to the iron throne
body:
Jon has no claim to the iron throne

None at all. The targaryens were overthrown, Robert Baratheon was the king and his legitimate kids would be the rightful heir to the throne. But Robert doesn’t have any. Therefore there is no rightful heir to the throne(I guess Cersei’s kids would be the rightful heir at this time actually). It does not work like that. Jon can fight for the throne back, but he is not the rightful heir. At all. In any way because it doesnt work that way.

Jon doesnt have more claim to the throne over Daenerys because as I said, the Targaryens are not on the throne. If Daenerys wants the throne, she has claim to it. Jon cant order Daenerys to stop going after the throne because he wants it or because hes Rheagers son and feels that he because of that hes the only one who should be on the throne. That’s stupid and makes zero sense. Daenerys cant feel threatened because Jon has no claim to that throne. At all. It just makes me annoyed that people keep saying that and the show is trying to build that up when it doesn’t work that way. Like honestly, if Robert knew Jon was Rheagers son and ned convinced Robert to keep Jon alive, would Jon be on the throne, or would Robert still be the king.

Theres no true heir. Unless the show Is that cliche, and let’s be honest, Jon and Daenerys are the most cliche characters in the entire show, then Jon is only being claimed as the true heir because of a cliche

On top of that, can people stop claiming that Jon has some sort of ownership of Daenerys’s dragons. She is their mother. Jon snow is someone they just met. They will not betray her for Jon snow. (I mean, I guess they would because I don’t know how dragons loyalty works in this world)

summary: I feel I have to remind people that what makes book!Jon a good character isn't that he defies the traditional protagonist role,...
body:
I feel I have to remind people that what makes book!Jon a good character isn’t that he defies the traditional protagonist role, but that his circumstances don’t adhere to it.

Jon Snow is very much an average guy doing his best out of a sense of honor, duty, and justice, but what makes those efforts worth something is the fact that he has to actually try. He doesn’t trip into responsibility and find he has a gift for it, he proves himself, he makes mistakes, and he pays for them.

The formula for a protagonist isn’t necessarily a bad one; it’s the lack of effort that goes into it that makes it cheap.

summary: Game of Thrones SPOILERS
body:
Game of Thrones SPOILERS

Now im thiking that all The girl Power they give us in episode3 was meaningless and without being made “from the heart” with the real intention of them go equal with the male characters

Why? there are 3 female power figures in Got. Cersei, Dany and Sansa.

Cersei is crazy now, but it is consistent with everything she has gone through, from the prophecies to the loss of Tommem

Sansa is, even by her own brother, placed in inferior position.

“She’s not as smart as she thinks” - says Jon Snow who’s alive because of Sansa.

And Dany who will become Mad Queen in 3 episodes, ignoring a whole 7 seasons journey. For what? so that she does not stand on the throne and to magnify Jon Snow’s arc

Fucking hell!

They did the “Girl Power” just to have the excuse, saying they are not sexist because they had episode 3 …

Im so mad with this shit!

I wasnt this mad when Ned died. Or when Theon betrays Robb. Or when Red Wedding happen…

I hate You DeD for fucked up One of The best tv shows today.

Since they are popping back up remember kids: DONT LISTEN TO THE 2017 LEAKS.

All they got right was the first episode. They said ep 2 was the Battle of Winterfell and that Bran and Meera die. No. No it didn’t. They couldn’t get any of that right, how would they get the ending right?

body:
J*nsa fans: I’m forever great I stan the Starks.

House Stark fans that don’t ship J*nsa: We love House Stark but we still can see the leaks are awful. Loving House Stark doesn’t mean we are blind to all the shit storytelling we are seeing this season (more like the past two seasons). You are only happy because you think Jon loves Sansa (nonsense) and the girl you hate might go mad. You don’t care about the show. You just want to see someone destroyed.
